Through further research, I discovered that medical expenses related to elderly falls cost our health system billions of dollars annually. While there are strategies for prevention, current investments in federal fall prevention programs are too small.

We have over 365,000 seniors living in Palm Beach County, and one of them is very special to memy 96-year-old mother.

After her recent fall and recovery, I learned that she was one of 36 million older Americans who fall every year.
